reviews.review_text: My grandparents stayed here about 3 years ago during peak COVID when they came back for quarantine. I know Im late on this review but my grandparents loved the place. The rooms were spacious, clean, and friendly, It also includes a kitchen so thats a bonus. Excellent place Rooms: Spacious and modern Easy to operate
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Never too late for good news. I am glad we were able to be there for them at a tough time!  Thanks for sharing.

reviews.review_text: I recently stayed at 2400 Motel in Vancouver, and it was a great experience. The staff was friendly, the room was clean and comfortable, and the location was convenient. I highly recommend it!

This was way back in 1979. One week stay in a one bedroom suite that had a small kitchen with sitting area as well. People were very friendly and helpful. Cleaning lady was there the very next day and we struck up a friendly conversation. I was new to BC and she told me where to get groceries and household needs at the best prices. I mentioned that I was quite cold the night before and I guess that she mentioned it to the front desk after she was done with my rooms because someone from the front desk came by with two extra blankets for me a few hours later. Those were the days when people were kinder I guess . I dont know how it is now but my stay there was great. The room was fine if somewhat dated, but still  cozy. Good location for getting around.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Aww thanks so much for the memory! Youll have to come back and visit.

reviews.review_text: Good place to stay with reasonable prices. No issues. Front desk girl was very kind and friendly to get along with :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Christopher! See you next time~

reviews.review_text: A great stay.  Cheap, cheerful and recently renovated makes me happy I choose this place to stay.  Very quaint old school experience and in the heart of the major city of Vancouver too.
Love the nostalgia of this place staff were helpful and courteous stayed for 3 nights with my very beautiful girlfriend courtney we loved every minute there together i love you courtney

It has been many decades since I stayed at the 2400. I liked the central location and the privacy of the intimate bungalows. When I stayed at the 2400 there was no such thing as internet, the fax was not yet invented. Music was on eight-track tapes and AM Radio. I often wonder if much has changed at the 2400?
The attendant was hilarious and she booked need in when I called. The place was dated but it was clean and spacious. It was super cool to stay in a place so many celebrities had also been.

Nice hotel. Good price. The front desk is really helpful with anything we needed. A bit out dated. But liked the hotel reminds me of the old hotels. Going to stay here again the next time Im in Vancouver. Its close to metrotown mall. The street in front of the hotel is quiet.

Seven days spent in total relaxation. This motel is my favorite in all of Vancouver. The chamber maids are so helpful, appropriate and hardworking... I took special care to leave my room as close to how it was when I checked in... Thanks 2400!!!
Never been here but they filmed X-Files season 3 Episode 23 here.  Well parts of it here.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: We sure did! We have been a great filming site for ages, and that legacy continues! Thanks for highlighting it :)

reviews.review_text: Clean, full kitchen, exactly as advertised, also very accommodating as my reservation was made for 6 people but we arrived with 7 and they allowed it without any hassle. About 15 minutes from the Nanaimo and 29th Avenue SkyTrain stations. We were only given 2 keys between 7 people though, and theres only 1 parking spot per suite so keep that in mind if those things will effect your plans.
Great location and nice service. In this motel, some movie and serie scenes were filmed (Bates Motel, X-Files...). High recommendable!
Staff are friendly, professional and just plain nice. Rooms are clean and comfortable. I love this place!
